        "content": "from priorityQueue import PriorityQueue\nimport math\n\n\ndef a_star(graph, start, goal, heuristic):\n    '''\n    Implementation of the A* search algorithm for computing the shortest\n    path between two vertices on a graph with non-negative edge weights.\n    The graph may be directed or undirected.\n\n    Inputs:\n    [graph]: tuple (G, w) where G is a graph.Graph instance and w is a\n             mapping of each edge to its non-negative weight (the pair\n             returned by graph.create_graph()).\n    [start]: graph.Vertex instance of G \u2014 the source vertex.\n    [goal]: graph.Vertex instance of G \u2014 the target vertex.\n    [heuristic]: callable taking a graph.Vertex and returning a numeric\n                 estimate of the remaining distance from that vertex to\n                 [goal]. Must be admissible (never overestimate the true\n                 remaining distance) for the returned path to be optimal.\n\n    Outputs:\n    [path]: list of vertices from start to goal (inclusive) along the\n            shortest path. Empty list if goal is unreachable from start.\n    [length]: total weight of the returned path.\n              math.inf if goal is unreachable from start.\n    '''\n    G, w = graph\n\n    g_score = {vertex: math.inf for vertex in G.vertices()}\n    g_score[start] = 0\n    came_from = {vertex: None for vertex in G.vertices()}\n\n    p_queue = PriorityQueue()\n    p_queue.add(start, heuristic(start))\n\n    while True:\n        try:\n            current = p_queue.pop()\n        except KeyError:\n            # queue drained without reaching goal \u2014 goal is unreachable\n            return [], math.inf\n\n        if current == goal:\n            path = []\n            node = goal\n            while node is not None:\n                path.append(node)\n                node = came_from[node]\n            path.reverse()\n            return path, g_score[goal]\n\n        for edge in G.incident_edges(current, outgoing=True):\n            neighbor = edge.opposite(current)\n            tentative = g_score[current] + w[edge]\n            if tentative < g_score[neighbor]:\n                # relaxation step\n                g_score[neighbor] = tentative\n                came_from[neighbor] = current\n                # priority is f = g + h; PriorityQueue.add updates if present\n                p_queue.add(neighbor, tentative + heuristic(neighbor))\n",
